### Agenda
- Review system functionalities and input-to-output flow  
- Discuss chatbot inquiry and complaint handling logic  
- Receive mentor guidance on model usage and deployment  

---

### Discussion and Decisions

| Issue / Agenda Item | Resolution / Action Item | Resolution Date |
|--------------------|--------------------------|-----------------|
| Inquiry vs Complaint Classification | User input should first be classified as an inquiry or a complaint, determining the system flow and response logic. | 16/01/2026 |
| Inquiry Handling & Fallback Logic | Inquiry handling should rely on rule-based logic and database matching. If confidence is low, the chatbot should stop and trigger form-based complaint or ticket creation. | 16/01/2026 |
| Use of Machine Learning | Machine learning should be used selectively (e.g., classification and entity recognition) alongside rule-based logic. | 16/01/2026 |
| Application & Deployment Strategy | A responsive web application was recommended over a standalone mobile app. Hosting options such as Vercel and external domains were discussed. | 16/01/2026 |

---

### Next Steps
- Refine system flow diagrams separating inquiries and complaints  
- Adjust chatbot logic to combine rules and limited ML  
- Continue frontend and backend development based on refined architecture  

